    "][div align="center" style="margin:15px 0 25px 0; padding:10px;"][img style="width:450px; height:auto;"]https://i.imgur.com/Rd4V1im.png[/img]
            [span style="
            font-size:25px;
            font-family:Garamond, serif;
            font-weight:bold; 
            color:#FFD700; 
            text-transform:uppercase; 
            letter-spacing:1px;
            text-shadow:0 0 1px #5a4614, 1px 1px 2px #7b6119;"]Prologue[/span]
        [/div]

        [div style="
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        color:#E0E0E0;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div id=pld-role style="font-size:20px; color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]The Paladin's Role
            [url=#top style="font-size:14px; color:#2980B9"]▲ Back to top ▲[/url]
        [/div]
    [/div]

            The Paladin stands at the forefront of battle, protecting allies by absorbing attacks and keeping enemies focused on them. With strong defense, mastery of shield blocking, and effective tools for managing and maintaining aggro, they ensure their team’s safety against any threat.

            [color=#cea425][b]Key Strengths:[/b][/color]  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Exceptional Defense:[/color] High shield block rate and damage mitigation keep the Paladin durable on the frontlines.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Strong Aggro Control:[/color] Reliable tools for maintaining enemy focus on both single targets and groups.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Self-Sustain:[/color] Healing enhanced by Majesty reduces reliance on party healers.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Team-Oriented Play:[/color] Protects teammates by mitigating damage and reducing pressure on healers.

            [color=#cea425][b]Challenges:[/b][/color]  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Aggro Management Practice:[/color] Maintaining Enmity through proper rotation of Job Abilities and Spells requires experience and timing.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Positioning Awareness:[/color] Optimal positioning is key for effective shield blocking and AoE Enmity control.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Equipment Dependency:[/color] The Paladin's performance heavily relies on using gear optimized for specific situations.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Skill Mastery:[/color] Requires a good grasp of Enmity mechanics, cooldown timings, and sub-job synergies.  
            • [color=#F7D58B]Leadership and Knowledge:[/color] A solid understanding of events, objectives, and strategies is essential, as Paladins often lead the group and initiate pulls.

            [color=#cea425][b]Role Versatility:[/b][/color]  
            With their versatility and powerful Defensive capabilities, Paladins excel in various situations.  
            They are the best tank for Dynamis Divergence and other content featuring physical damage bosses, while also being capable of mitigating magical damage when a Rune Fencer is unavailable.
        [/div]
        

        [div style="
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        color:#E0E0E0;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div id=pld-subjob style="
                font-size:20px; 
                color: #cea425; 
                text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]Sub-Job
                    [url=#top style="font-size:14px; color:#2980B9"]▲ Back to top ▲[/url]
                [/div]
            [/div]

            The choice of sub-job for a Paladin depends on the content and your role in the group. While Blue Mage dominates as the most versatile and universally effective sub-job, others like Rune Fencer and Scholar offer situational advantages in niche scenarios. Below is an analysis of the most popular Sub-Jobs, highlighting their strengths, weaknesses, and practical usage.

            [div align="center"][table style="border:3px ridge #b08d57; box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px #5b4b2d;"]
                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #b79b4f 0%, #806a35 100%); box-shadow: inset 0 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);"]
                        [th colspan="7" style="text-align:center; font-size:18px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold; color:#332b05; text-shadow:0 0 1px #806a35, 0px 0px 2px #b7974d;"]Top Tier[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"][th style="color:#FFD700; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; text-transform:uppercase; vertical-align:middle;"]Sub-Job[/th]
                        [th style="color:#FFD700; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; text-transform:uppercase; vertical-align:middle;"]Strengths[/th]
                        [th style="color:#FFD700; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; text-transform:uppercase; vertical-align:middle;"]Weaknesses[/th]
                        [th style="color:#FFD700; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; text-transform:uppercase; vertical-align:middle;"]Usage[/th][/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                        [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/MBRDSOd.png[/img]
                            [color=#ffda75]Blue Mage[/color]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• High defense with Cocoon  
                            • Versatile AoE enmity tools  
                            • Great for multi-target tanking
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Requires specific spells  
                            • Slightly lower DPS potential
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• All-purpose sub, excels in most content[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                        [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/M48LBoB.png[/img]
                            [color=#ffda75]Rune Fencer[/color]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Strong magical defense (Runes)  
                            • Foil, Valiance, Vallation for enmity
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Weaker physical defense (no Cocoon)  
                            • Limited AoE tools
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Ideal for magic-heavy fights or niche roles[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #b79b4f 0%, #806a35 100%); box-shadow: inset 0 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);"]
                        [th colspan="7" style="text-align:center; font-size:18px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold; color:#332b05; text-shadow:0 0 1px #806a35, 0px 0px 2px #b7974d;"]Mid Tier[/th]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                        [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/FWXf6Vb.png[/img]
                            [color=#ffda75]Scholar[/color]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• AoE buffs (Phalanx, Regen, etc.)  
                            • Good utility (Sublimation, Stoneskin)
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• No direct enmity tools  
                            • Niche usage (Aminon, group support)
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Mainly support in special scenarios[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                        [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/qQBSdaY.png[/img]
                            [color=#ffda75]Red Mage[/color]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• AoE XP farming (Aeolian Edge)  
                            • Self-buffs (Haste, Refresh)
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Weak for tanking endgame  
                            • Limited group utility
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Niche AoE farming sub[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                        [td style="color:#E0E0E0; text-align:center; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"][img]https://i.imgur.com/5mCKggF.png[/img]
                            [color=#ffda75]Warrior[/color]
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Solid enmity from Provoke, Warcry  
                            • Simple, DPS-friendly sub
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Less survivability than BLU  
                            • No AoE enmity or magic defense
                        [/td]
                        [td style="text-align:left; border-right:1px solid #707070; padding:5px; vertical-align:middle;"]• Casual content or extra damage[/td]
                    [/tr]
                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #b79b4f 0%, #806a35 100%); box-shadow: inset 0 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);"]
