            [table][tr][td]For this [color=#F7D58B][b]high-tier idle MDT configuration[/b][/color], I offer a single optimized set:

                            • [color=#cea425][b]Optimized Magic Damage Taken Set[/b][/color]
                            This set is specifically designed for maximum [color=#F7D58B]magic damage[/color] mitigation, tailored for [color=#F7D58B]End Game[/color] content where high-level [color=#F7D58B]magical threats[/color] are prevalent. It prioritizes [color=#F7D58B]Magic Defense Bonus (MDB)[/color], [color=#F7D58B]Magic Evasion[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]elemental resistances[/color] to provide the best possible protection against [color=#F7D58B]magical damage[/color]. Due to the specialized nature of this setup, [color=#F7D58B]Low[/color] and [color=#F7D58B]Mid Tier[/color] versions are not included, as they offer limited effectiveness in such scenarios.

                            Additionally, [color=#F7D58B][b]alternative gear options[/b][/color] will be provided for players who may not have access to all optimal pieces, ensuring flexibility while maintaining strong [color=#F7D58B]magical defense[/color].

                            This configuration ensures you're fully prepared to withstand even the most intense [color=#F7D58B]magical assaults[/color] in [color=#F7D58B]high-end encounters[/color].
                        [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
