        color:#E0E0E0;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div id=pld-idle-xp style="font-size:20px; color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]IDLE XP
                    [url=#top style="font-size:14px; color:#2980B9"]▲ Back to top ▲[/url]
                [/div]
            [/div]

            [table][tr][td]For this [color=#F7D58B]Idle XP set at Crawler's Nest [S][/color], it is a [color=#F7D58B]classic Idle PDT set[/color] optimized with the [color=#66ccff]full Chevalier's set[/color] [size=12][i]"In this area, the body armor bug against Fomors does not occur"[/i][/size], allowing it to be used safely and fully benefit from the set bonus [size=12][i]"Occasionally Absorbs Damage Taken"[/i][/size], providing a [color=#7fe07f]5% chance to recover HP[/color].

                    With over 100 enemies engaged during the pull and since the player is often facing away, the proc activates regularly, offering effective passive regeneration during the gathering phases.
                [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [div align="center"][div align="center"][table][tr][td vertical-align="middle" style="padding:0px 10px; text-align:center;"][table style="border:3px ridge #b08d57; box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px #5b4b2d;"]
                                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                                        [th colspan="7" style="text-align:center; font-size:18px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold; color:#332b05; text-shadow:0 0 1px #806a35, 0px 0px 2px #b7974d;"]IDLE XP[/th]
                                    [/tr]
                                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                                        [td][itemset]397864[/itemset][/td]
                                        [td style="padding:5px; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][div style="text-align:left; display:inline-block; line-height:1.5;"]• PDT II: -68%
