        [div style="
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        color:#E0E0E0;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div id=pld-idle-town style="font-size:20px; color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]IDLE REFRESH / TOWN
                    [url=#top style="font-size:14px; color:#2980B9"]▲ Back to top ▲[/url]
                [/div]
            [/div]

            [table][tr][td]For the [b][color=#F7D58B]Idle Refresh / Town set[/color][/b], this setup is designed specifically for resting in safe zones or town areas where there is no danger. It focuses on maximizing [b]MP and HP regeneration[/b] while maintaining a balanced pool of both. The use of [color=#66ccff]Carmine Cuisses +1[/color] in the leg slot is purely for the [color=#F7D58B][b]+18% movement speed[/b][/color] boost, allowing faster movement around town. This configuration ensures efficient recovery and quick mobility during downtime.
                [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [div align="center"][div align="center"][table][tr][td vertical-align="middle" style="padding:0px 10px; text-align:center;"][table style="border:3px ridge #b08d57; box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px #5b4b2d;"]
                                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                                        [th colspan="7" style="text-align:center; font-size:18px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold; color:#332b05; text-shadow:0 0 1px #806a35, 0px 0px 2px #b7974d;"]IDLE REFRESH / TOWN[/th]
                                    [/tr]
                                    [tr style="background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5);"]
                                        [td][itemset]397548[/itemset][/td]
                                        [td style="padding:5px; border-bottom:1px solid #707070; border-right:1px solid #707070; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle;"][div style="text-align:left; display:inline-block; line-height:1.5;"]• Refresh: +6
                                            • Regen: +1
                                            • Movement Speed: +18%
                                            • HP: +986
                                            • MP: +311[/div][/td]
                            [/tr][/table][/div][/div][/div]
    [/div]
    
    
    [div style="
    margin:0 auto; 
    background-color:rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.85); 
    padding:5px; 
    border-radius:15px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1); 
    border:3px ridge #F7D58B;
    "][div align="center" style="margin:15px 0 25px 0; padding:10px;"][img style="width:450px; height:auto;"]https://i.imgur.com/Rd4V1im.png[/img]
            [span style="
            font-size:25px;
            font-family:Garamond, serif;
            font-weight:bold; 
            color:#FFD700; 
            text-transform:uppercase; 
            letter-spacing:1px;
            text-shadow:0 0 1px #5a4614, 1px 1px 2px #7b6119;"]Enmity Set Overview[/span][/div]
        [div align="left"]The [color=#F7D58B][b]Enmity Set[/b][/color] is designed to maximize threat generation and maintain enemy focus. 
            This setup prioritizes [color=#ff7f50]Enmity+[/color] gear to ensure consistent hate retention, allowing for full control over aggressive targets. 
            Key elements include stacking [color=#F7D58B]VIT[/color], [color=#F7D58B]HP[/color], and maintaining capped [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color] and [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color] 
            to reduce incoming damage while generating maximum enmity.

            [color=#cea425][b]Conclusion[/b][/color]
            The Enmity Set is essential for holding aggro by maximizing threat generation while ensuring damage mitigation 
            through capped defenses and solid defensive stats.
        [/div]

        [div style="
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); 
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 1), 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        color:#E0E0E0;
        text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div id=pld-full-enmity style="font-size:20px; color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]Full Enmity Set
                    [url=#top style="font-size:14px; color:#2980B9"]▲ Back to top ▲[/url]
                [/div]
            [/div]

            [table][tr][td]The [color=#66ccff]Full Enmity Set[/color] is intended for shorter, rapid spells or [color=#e5d522]Job Abilities (JAs)[/color] (e.g. [color=#00ffd0]Flash[/color], [color=#00ffd0]Jettatura[/color]) with a low chance of interruption. It maximizes [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] while maintaining a [color=#7fe07f]~3000 HP pool[/color] and staying sufficiently tanky.

                        • [color=#F7D58B]PDT & MDT[/color]: Ideally, aim to cap both physical and magical damage reduction.  
                        • [color=#7fe07f]~3000 HP Pool[/color]: Ensures a healthy HP total for survivability.  
                        • [color=#ff7f50]Maximize Enmity[/color]: Focus on boosting threat without sacrificing the above stats.

                        By focusing on [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] for quick, essential abilities and fast-casting spells while preserving robust defense and HP this set achieves high threat generation without compromising durability.
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [div align="center"][div align="center"][table][tr][td vertical-align="middle" style="padding:0px 10px; text-align:center;"][table style="border:3px ridge #b08d57; box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px #5b4b2d;"]
                                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                                        [th colspan="7" style="text-align:center; font-size:18px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold; color:#332b05; text-shadow:0 0 1px #806a35, 0px 0px 2px #b7974d;"]Full Enmity Set[/th]
                                    [/tr]
