            [table][tr][td]The [color=#66ccff]Fast Cast Set[/color] is designed exclusively for the [color=#F7D58B]Precast[/color] phase to minimize spell casting time. This set does not impact [color=#e5d522]Job Abilities (JAs)[/color] and is solely focused on reducing the casting time of spells.

                        [color=#cea425][b]Defensive Considerations[/b][/color]  
                        Since this set is equipped very briefly through [color=#F7D58B]Gearswap[/color], defensive stats like [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color], [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color] are irrelevant. I have never noticed any unusually high damage taken during the transition into Fast Cast gear with [color=#F7D58B]Gearswap[/color].

                        [color=#cea425][b]Fast Cast Cap and HP Comparison[/b][/color]  
                        This set is capped at [color=#F7D58B]80% Fast Cast[/color] to achieve the shortest possible spell casting time. Although it has the lowest HP pool among all sets, it remains reasonable with [color=#7fe07f]2938 HP[/color] compared to [color=#7fe07f]3057 HP[/color] in Idle for an Elvaan.

                        [color=#cea425][b]Alternative Options[/b][/color]  
                        Showing alternative sets other than the BiS seems unnecessary for this specific purpose. However, I will still suggest other Fast Cast gear options below for those seeking:
                        • A tankier setup with higher defensive stats.  
                        • A more generalized configuration for players not using [color=#F7D58B]Gearswap[/color].
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
