            [span style="
            font-size:25px;
            font-family:Garamond, serif;
            font-weight:bold; 
            color:#FFD700; 
            text-transform:uppercase; 
            letter-spacing:1px;
            text-shadow:0 0 1px #5a4614, 1px 1px 2px #7b6119;"]CURE SETS Overview[/span][/div]
        [div align="left"][color=#66ccff]Cure Sets[/color] are specialized setups designed to optimize healing in combat, balancing efficiency, survivability, and reliability. These sets focus on leveraging [color=#F7D58B]Cure Potency[/color], [color=#F7D58B]SIRD (Spell Interruption Rate Down)[/color], and strong defensive stats like [color=#F7D58B]PDT[/color], [color=#F7D58B]MDT[/color], and [color=#F7D58B]DT[/color] reductions to ensure uninterrupted and effective healing, regardless of the situation.

                [color=#cea425][b]There are two distinct types of Cure Sets:[/b][/color]
                • [color=#66ccff]Cure Self Set[/color]: Optimized for self-healing, it maximizes HP during midcast to enable powerful recovery, even when at full health. This set focuses on maintaining high [color=#F7D58B]Enmity[/color] and tankiness, ensuring that the caster remains resilient during combat.  
                • [color=#66ccff]Cure Other Set[/color]: Designed for healing allies, it prioritizes consistent performance without requiring a large HP pool. This set focuses on reliable [color=#F7D58B]Cure Potency[/color] and strong defensive stats to ensure the caster can safely support their team.

                Both sets play a crucial role in maintaining survivability and healing efficiency, tailored to meet the specific demands of self-healing or team support during combat.
        [/div]

        [div style="
        background-color:rgba(254, 254, 254, 0.1); 
        padding:10px; 
        border-radius:10px; 
        border:2px ridge rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); 
