        text-align:left;"][div align="center"][div id=pld-ws-atonement style="font-size:20px; color: #cea425; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px 10px #967616;"]ATONEMENT
                    [url=#top style="font-size:14px; color:#2980B9"]▲ Back to top ▲[/url]
                [/div]
            [/div]

            [table][tr][td][color=#F7D58B]Atonement[/color] is a Weapon Skill designed solely to generate high amounts of [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color]. Its effectiveness is based on [color=#F7D58B]cumulative (CE)[/color] and [color=#F7D58B]volatile (VE)[/color] [color=#ff7f50]enmity[/color], making it a key tool for maintaining aggro.

                Unlike traditional Weapon Skills, Atonement focuses entirely on maximizing [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] rather than dealing high damage. Higher [color=#F7D58B]TP[/color] further enhances its enmity multiplier, reaching 3x at 3000 TP with the right gear.

                The Atonement Set is built to maximize [color=#ff7f50]Enmity[/color] while maintaining tankiness, ensuring optimal threat generation in combat. Below is an optimized setup for this purpose.
                    [/td]
                [/tr]
            [/table]
            [div align="center"][div align="center"][table][tr][td vertical-align="middle" style="padding:0px 10px; text-align:center;"][table style="border:3px ridge #b08d57; box-shadow: inset 0 0 6px #5b4b2d;"]
                                    [tr style="background: linear-gradient(to top, #b08d57, #806a38); box-shadow: inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);"]
                                        [th colspan="7" style="text-align:center; font-size:18px; text-transform:uppercase; font-weight:bold; color:#332b05; text-shadow:0 0 1px #806a35, 0px 0px 2px #b7974d;"]ATONEMENT[/th]
                                    [/tr]
